The paper deals with stereo estimation using a hybrid CNN+CRF model and proposes a method to train the model on large-scale data end-to-end. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a theoretically sound method based on the structured output support vector machine (SSVM) to train the model, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a highly parallel dual block descent algorithm for inference, which suggests that it may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the model on challenging stereo benchmarks, which suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
